in Tarbagatai Mtn. Range.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBCDF5AB7738FFF9FF1EFB3F0FAE4EBA" pageId="3" pageNumber="384" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A368A6207738FFF9FF1EFB3F0FAE4EBA" blockId="3.[151,1437,798,1221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis id="91A37A327738FFF9FF1EFB3F0A504EDF" bold="true" box="[199,353,1158,1184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="384">Distribution.</emphasis>
Eastern 
<collectingCountry id="DBC0E6B07738FFF9FE11FB3E097F4EDE" box="[456,590,1159,1185]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="3" pageNumber="384">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, Southern Siberia, the Russian Far East. In Southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="DBC0E6B07738FFF9FB3DFB3E0E564EDE" box="[1252,1383,1159,1185]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="3" pageNumber="384">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
was found in the eastern part of Dzhungarsky Alatau Mtn. Range and on Tarbagatai Mtn. Range.
</paragraph>
